                            <comment id="220172" author="jfilizetti" created="Tue, 6 Feb 2018 19:28:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch at &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/31095&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/31095&lt;/a&gt; breaks the ability to build SSK due to a script error:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;checking for krb5_derive_key in -lgssapi_krb5... no&lt;br/&gt;
./configure: line 21783: xyes: command not found&lt;br/&gt;
checking whether OpenSSL has functions needed for SSK... no&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is due to the second part of the if statement after the &amp;amp;&amp;amp;:&lt;br/&gt;
AS_IF(&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;test &amp;quot;x$gss_conf_test&amp;quot; = xsuccess &amp;amp;&amp;amp; &amp;quot;x$enable_gss&amp;quot; != xno&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, [&lt;/p&gt;

